oai_dc:dc.dc:title: Image of Maj. William Jere Crook, Confederate doctor
oai_dc:dc.dc:description: Maj. Crook served in Co. I, 13th Tenn. Inf. CSA, "Forked Deer Volunteers" from Middlefork, Mifflin, and Jacks Creek, Tenn. Major Crook was wounded at Murfreesboro while serving as the captain of Company I. He was later promoted to major.
